# Component Structure and Organization

## Source Layout

All web source in `web/src/`:

- **Components**: `web/src/components/` (shadcn primitives in `ui/`)
- **Pages**: `web/src/pages/{FeatureNamePage}/`
- **Store**: `web/src/store/`

## Shared Component Structure

```
web/src/components/ComponentName/
├── index.ts
├── ComponentName.tsx
├── IComponentName.ts
└── ComponentName.styles.ts   # optional CVA/Tailwind constants
```

## Page Structure (context-based)

```
web/src/pages/FeatureNamePage/
├── index.ts
├── FeatureNamePage.tsx              # ProtectedRoute + Provider
├── FeatureNamePageContainer/
│   ├── FeatureNamePageContainer.tsx
│   └── SubComponent/
├── context/
│   ├── FeatureNamePageContext.ts
│   ├── FeatureNamePageProvider.tsx  # orchestrates hooks only
│   └── hooks/
│       ├── api/useFetchFeaturePageData.ts
│       ├── useFeaturePageHandlers.ts
│       ├── useFeaturePageEffects.ts
│       └── useFeaturePageContext.ts
├── types/
└── utils/
```

## Rules

- **Providers**: orchestrate hooks only — no `useState`, `useSelector`, or `useEffect` directly
- **Containers**: consume context, early return for loading/error, render UI
- **Redux**: `useSelector` in components/hooks, not prop drilling
- **Interfaces**: prefix with `I` (e.g., `IDocumentsPageContext`)
- **Exports**: named exports for all components
- **Handlers**: prefix with `handle` (e.g., `handleSubmit`)

## Page Template

```typescript
export const DocumentsPage = () => (
  <ProtectedRoute>
    <DocumentsPageProvider>
      <DocumentsPageContainer />
    </DocumentsPageProvider>
  </ProtectedRoute>
);
```

